http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Government-submits-compliance-report-to-HC-in-students%E2%80%99-transfer-case/article13982593.ece

The State government on Monday submitted a compliance report in the Orissa High Court stating that in pursuant to its (HC’s) earlier orders, all the 124 medicos of the now-defunct Sardar Rajas Medical College in Kalahandi district have been transferred to other medical colleges of the State.An official of the State Health and Family Welfare department in an affidavit informed the High Court that 109 medicos were transferred to two government medical colleges while remaining 15 were transferred to three private medical colleges of the State.“The entire process of transfers was completed by December 23 last as per the directions of the High Court,” the compliance report said.